<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1041" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1041">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Count <persName type="from">de Lichtervelde</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Belgium</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-18"><hi rend="italic">February 18,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have to-day received
                            a telegram charging me to express to your excellency the very sorrowful
                            emotion and the grievous sympathy of the King and of Belgium in
                            connection with the catastrophe to the <hi rend="italic">Maine.</hi></p>
                        <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lichtervelde.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>